          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced shallot</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced shallot </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until crispy – this is your <strong>crispy shallot</strong></p><p>Once crispy, transfer them to a small bowl or plate<strong> </strong>and reserve the pan</p>",
